// Gap 2.4 repro fixture — companion module for a.ach.
//
// The only exported fn is `middle`, whose body references
// `helper()` as a BARE identifier (not `b::helper`). Inside
// this module, `helper` resolves to the module-private
// declaration below. When the VM compiler recursively walks
// this module, both `helper` and `middle` land in
// `fn_decl_asts` with the mangled `b::` prefix, so the
// ProveIR fn_table gets `b::helper` and `b::middle` — but
// middle's body AST still has the raw `helper()` parser
// output. See a.ach for the repro scenario.

fn helper() { 1 }

export fn middle() { helper() }
